    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-04-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-04-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="636"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d636">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.796/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-04-19T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 21—11 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Department’s telegram 6, January 25, 7 p.m. President Leguia assures me that
                    the persistent reports that the Peruvian Government has signed contract with
                    German aeronautical interests to operate in Peru are not true and says that the
                    present intention is to enter into contracts with both American and German
                    interests and let them compete.…</p>
                <p>Detailed report concerning Woolman’s negotiations are contained in despatch
                    mailed April 18th.<note n="81" xml:id="d636fn81">Presumably despatch No. 932,
                        Apr. 16, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
